# Phase 12: Figma-First Design & Asset Integration

## Objective
The user has requested the integration of actual AI-generated imagery into the `jin-hong-me-html-v2` website and the application of Figma-standard UI/UX updates across all pages, page by page. This represents a mature "Master Tier" implementation.

## Proposed Changes

### [Component] Asset Generation & Management
#### [NEW] `C:\Users\user\Desktop\antigravity\ai_image_resources\`
- **Generate AI Images**: 
  - `hero_data_center.webp`: Cinematic shot of an illuminated server room (Dark/Onyx tones, blue accents).
  - `hero_cleanroom.webp`: High-tech cleanroom facility with personnel in suits.
  - `about_engineering.webp`: Blueprint/engineering schematics overlay on a modern industrial site.
- **Image Linking**: Move images into the `jin-hong-me-html-v2/images/` directory and update the `src` references in the HTML files.

### [Component] Figma Layout Standards (CSS)
#### [MODIFY] `css/global.css`
- Apply `figma-automation` defined spacing rules (e.g., rigid base-8 token system where applicable).
- Enhance the shadow system to use layered, diffused shadows rather than harsh drop shadows.
- Verify typography hierarchy (Line-heights, letter-spacing) against Figma optimal standards.

### [Component] Page-by-Page HTML Figma Sweep
#### [MODIFY] `index.html`
- Replace `images/slider-2.jpg`, `slider-3.jpg` and `images/corporate/about.jpg` with the generated high-fidelity assets.
- Ensure structural paddings and flex gaps align with the Figma baseline.

#### [MODIFY] `about.html`, `services.html`, etc.
- Sweep through each inner page sequentially, replacing empty/placeholder image tags with relevant generated photos or CSS visual equivalents.

## Verification Plan
- Run local server / check browser logic.
- Verify all images load (No `placehold.co`).
- Verify the layout feels tighter and more aligned with high-fidelity Figma files.
